{"created":"2015-01-23T18:27:09+00:00","modified":"2015-01-23T19:20:44+00:00","valid":{"from":"2015-01-23T19:20:44+00:00","to":"3015-01-23T19:20:44+00:00"},"hreflang":"en","title":"Remembering The Children's Blizzard Of 1888","published":"2015-01-23T19:20:00+00:00","teaser":"At this time of year in 1888, people across the Upper Midwest were mourning the deaths of hundreds of people -- most of them children.","itags":["npr_api","379384003"],"guid":"4a7caccb-5f89-498a-8721-f38b5d4013cf","contentencoded":"<p><a href=\"//s3.amazonaws.com/media.wbur.org/wordpress/11/files/2015/01/0123_childrens-blizzard.jpeg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-76975\" src=\"//s3.amazonaws.com/media.wbur.org/wordpress/11/files/2015/01/0123_childrens-blizzard-199x300.jpeg\" alt=\"Cover of \"The Children's Blizzard by David Laskin\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" /></a></p><p>At this time of year in 1888, people across the Upper Midwest were mourning the deaths of hundreds of people in a snowstorm.</p><p>Most of them were children from pioneer families who came from Germany and Scandinavia.</p><p><strong>David Laskin</strong>&#8216;s book &#8220;<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Childrens-Blizzard-David-Laskin/dp/0060520760/\" target=\"_blank\">The Children&#8217;s Blizzard</a>&#8221; captures their stories. We revisit <em><a href=\"http://hereandnow.wbur.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Here & Now</a></em> host Robin Young&#8217;s conversation with Laskin on March 10, 2006.</p><h4>Guest</h4><ul><li><strong><a href=\"http://davidlaskin.com/\" target=\"_blank\">David Laskin</a></strong>, author of &#8220;The Children&#8217;s Blizzard.&#8221; He tweets <a href=\"https://twitter.com/davidlaskin\" target=\"_blank\">@davidlaskin</a>.</li></ul><h4><strong>Related</strong></h4><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.minnpost.com/minnesota-history/2013/01/125-years-ago-deadly-children-s-blizzard-blasted-minnesota\">125 years ago, deadly 'Childrenâ€™s Blizzard' blasted Minnesota</a></li></ul>  <div class=\"full